1 Switch project from Maven to Ant
  * put all jars into repository: spring, hibernate, hsql, jetty etc.
  * create ant build.xml and checkin ant tools
  * basic ant tasks creation: 
    - compile src, tests
    - run unit tests
    - java test coverage
    - prepare db
    - copy resources
    - package, deploy webapp
    - start, stop webapp
2 Install code static tool
     CheckStyle
     FindBugs
3 Install code visualization tool
     Toxicity
     Tree maps http://www.panopticode.org/gallery/index.html
4 Install Selenium
  * run selenium tests in ant
5 Install junit
6 Setup cruise and create pipeline
  * integrate unit tests result
  * integrate selenium tests
  * integrate code analysis tool result
7 Experiment distributed build
8 Setup cctray and big visible cruise monitor
9 Setup iAnalyze
10 Mingle latest version
  - postgresql, mysql
